cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on using SoundNet, a fully convolutional neural network trained on audio data, for anger detection in speech. This suggests that the paper could fall under the cs.SD sub-category. 
2. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with emotion detection in speech, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, it could also belong to the cs.CL sub-category. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses transfer learning to improve the performance of the anger detection model. This suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG sub-category. 
4. cs.SD (Signal Processing): The paper deals with processing audio signals for emotion detection, which could also fall under the cs.SD sub-category. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses deep learning techniques for emotion detection, which could also fall under the cs.AI sub-category.
